The paper deals with representing the suffix tree of a string using the compact directed acyclic word graph (CDAWG) and supporting various queries efficiently. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of heavy path decomposition, which is a technique commonly used in computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph algorithms (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper discusses the representation of a context-free grammar, which is a topic in both machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
